(firstQuint)Post - Hospital Syndrome: Profile of Functional Status by Malnutrition.

 The majority of geriatric hospitalized patients are at high risk for malnutrition at discharge, which has negative impact on post-hospital outcomes.

 In a cross-sectional analysis in malnourished, geriatric patients we will evaluate frailty-status and functional status using objective and subjective methods at hospital discharge.

 Moreover, we will investigate the association between nutritional Status and frailty, sarcopenia, quality of life and fatigue.

